Inductive token : Type :=
| XOR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| WHENOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| WHEN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| VAR_NAME : (LustreAst.ident * LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| VAR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT8 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT64 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT32 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT16 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| TRUE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| THEN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| TEL : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| STAR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| SLASH : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| SEMICOLON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RPAREN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RETURNS : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RESTART : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RARROW : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| PLUS : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| OR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ONOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| NOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| NODE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| NEQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| MOD : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| MINUS : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| MERGE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LXOR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LSR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LSL : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LPAREN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LOR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LNOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LET : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LEQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LAND : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT8 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT64 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT32 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT16 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| IFTE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| HASH : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| GT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| GEQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FUNCTION : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FLOAT64 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FLOAT32 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FBY : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FALSE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EVERY : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EOF : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ELSE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| DOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| CONSTANT : (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| COMMA : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| COLONCOLON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| COLON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| BOOL : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ASSERT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| AND : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token.

Definition terminal_semantic_type (t:terminal) : Type:=
  match t with
  | XOR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | WHENOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | WHEN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | VAR_NAME't => (LustreAst.ident * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | VAR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT8't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT64't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT32't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT16't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | TRUE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | THEN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | TEL't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | STAR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | SLASH't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | SEMICOLON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RPAREN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RETURNS't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RESTART't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RARROW't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | PLUS't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | OR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ONOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | NOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | NODE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | NEQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | MOD't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | MINUS't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | MERGE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LXOR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LSR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LSL't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LPAREN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LOR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LNOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LET't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LEQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LAND't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT8't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT64't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT32't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT16't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | IFTE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | HASH't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | GT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | GEQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FUNCTION't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FLOAT64't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FLOAT32't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FBY't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FALSE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EVERY't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EOF't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ELSE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | DOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | CONSTANT't => (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | COMMA't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | COLONCOLON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | COLON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | BOOL't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ASSERT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | AND't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  end.

Definition nonterminal_semantic_type (nt:nonterminal) : Type:=
  match nt with
  | when_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | var_decl_list'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls)%type
  | var_decl'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls)%type
  | unary_operator'nt => (LustreAst.unary_operator * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | unary_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | type_name'nt => (LustreAst.type_name * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | translation_unit_file'nt => (list LustreAst.declaration)%type
  | translation_unit'nt => (list LustreAst.declaration)%type
  | shift_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | relational_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | primary_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | postfix_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | pattern'nt => (list LustreAst.ident)%type
  | parameter_list'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls )%type
  | optsemicolon'nt => (unit)%type
  | oparameter_list'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls )%type
  | node_or_function'nt => (bool * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | multiplicative_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | logical_OR_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | logical_AND_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | local_var_decl'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls)%type
  | local_decl_list'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls)%type
  | local_decl'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls)%type
  | inclusive_OR_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | identifier_list'nt => (list LustreAst.ident )%type
  | fby_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | expression_list'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | exclusive_OR_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | equations'nt => (list LustreAst.equation)%type
  | equation'nt => (LustreAst.equation)%type
  | equality_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | declared_clock'nt => (LustreAst.preclock)%type
  | declaration'nt => (LustreAst.declaration)%type
  | constant'nt => (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | clock'nt => (LustreAst.clock)%type
  | cast_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | bool_constant'nt => (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | arrow_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | additive_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | AND_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  end.

Definition symbol_semantic_type (s:symbol) : Type:=
  match s with
  | T t => terminal_semantic_type t
  | NT nt => nonterminal_semantic_type nt
  end.

Definition token := token.

Definition token_term (tok : token) : terminal :=
  match tok with
  | XOR _ => XOR't
  | WHENOT _ => WHENOT't
  | WHEN _ => WHEN't
  | VAR_NAME _ => VAR_NAME't
  | VAR _ => VAR't
  | UINT8 _ => UINT8't
  | UINT64 _ => UINT64't
  | UINT32 _ => UINT32't
  | UINT16 _ => UINT16't
  | TRUE _ => TRUE't
  | THEN _ => THEN't
  | TEL _ => TEL't
  | STAR _ => STAR't
  | SLASH _ => SLASH't
  | SEMICOLON _ => SEMICOLON't
  | RPAREN _ => RPAREN't
  | RETURNS _ => RETURNS't
  | RESTART _ => RESTART't
  | RARROW _ => RARROW't
  | PLUS _ => PLUS't
  | OR _ => OR't
  | ONOT _ => ONOT't
  | ON _ => ON't
  | NOT _ => NOT't
  | NODE _ => NODE't
  | NEQ _ => NEQ't
  | MOD _ => MOD't
  | MINUS _ => MINUS't
  | MERGE _ => MERGE't
  | LXOR _ => LXOR't
  | LT _ => LT't
  | LSR _ => LSR't
  | LSL _ => LSL't
  | LPAREN _ => LPAREN't
  | LOR _ => LOR't
  | LNOT _ => LNOT't
  | LET _ => LET't
  | LEQ _ => LEQ't
  | LAND _ => LAND't
  | INT8 _ => INT8't
  | INT64 _ => INT64't
  | INT32 _ => INT32't
  | INT16 _ => INT16't
  | IFTE _ => IFTE't
  | HASH _ => HASH't
  | GT _ => GT't
  | GEQ _ => GEQ't
  | FUNCTION _ => FUNCTION't
  | FLOAT64 _ => FLOAT64't
  | FLOAT32 _ => FLOAT32't
  | FBY _ => FBY't
  | FALSE _ => FALSE't
  | EVERY _ => EVERY't
  | EQ _ => EQ't
  | EOF _ => EOF't
  | ELSE _ => ELSE't
  | DOT _ => DOT't
  | CONSTANT _ => CONSTANT't
  | COMMA _ => COMMA't
  | COLONCOLON _ => COLONCOLON't
  | COLON _ => COLON't
  | BOOL _ => BOOL't
  | ASSERT _ => ASSERT't
  | AND _ => AND't
  end.

Definition token_sem (tok : token) : symbol_semantic_type (T (token_term tok)) :=
  match tok with
  | XOR x => x
  | WHENOT x => x
  | WHEN x => x
  | VAR_NAME x => x
  | VAR x => x
  | UINT8 x => x
  | UINT64 x => x
  | UINT32 x => x
  | UINT16 x => x
  | TRUE x => x
  | THEN x => x
  | TEL x => x
  | STAR x => x
  | SLASH x => x
  | SEMICOLON x => x
  | RPAREN x => x
  | RETURNS x => x
  | RESTART x => x
  | RARROW x => x
  | PLUS x => x
  | OR x => x
  | ONOT x => x
  | ON x => x
  | NOT x => x
  | NODE x => x
  | NEQ x => x
  | MOD x => x
  | MINUS x => x
  | MERGE x => x
  | LXOR x => x
  | LT x => x
  | LSR x => x
  | LSL x => x
  | LPAREN x => x
  | LOR x => x
  | LNOT x => x
  | LET x => x
  | LEQ x => x
  | LAND x => x
  | INT8 x => x
  | INT64 x => x
  | INT32 x => x
  | INT16 x => x
  | IFTE x => x
  | HASH x => x
  | GT x => x
  | GEQ x => x
  | FUNCTION x => x
  | FLOAT64 x => x
  | FLOAT32 x => x
  | FBY x => x
  | FALSE x => x
  | EVERY x => x
  | EQ x => x
  | EOF x => x
  | ELSE x => x
  | DOT x => x
  | CONSTANT x => x
  | COMMA x => x
  | COLONCOLON x => x
  | COLON x => x
  | BOOL x => x
  | ASSERT x => x
  | AND x => x
  end.

Instance ProductionAlph : MenhirLib.Alphabet.Alphabet production := _.

Definition prod_contents (p:production) :
  { p:nonterminal * list symbol &
    MenhirLib.Grammar.arrows_right
      (symbol_semantic_type (NT (fst p)))
      (List.map symbol_semantic_type (snd p)) }
 :=
  let box := existT (fun p =>
    MenhirLib.Grammar.arrows_right
      (symbol_semantic_type (NT (fst p)))
      (List.map symbol_semantic_type (snd p)) )
  in
  match p with
  | Prod'AND_expression'0 => box
    (AND_expression'nt, [NT equality_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'AND_expression'1 => box
    (AND_expression'nt, [NT equality_expression'nt; T AND't; NT AND_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.BAND expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'additive_expression'0 => box
    (additive_expression'nt, [NT multiplicative_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'additive_expression'1 => box
    (additive_expression'nt, [NT multiplicative_expression'nt; T PLUS't; NT additive_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.ADD expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'additive_expression'2 => box
    (additive_expression'nt, [NT multiplicative_expression'nt; T MINUS't; NT additive_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.SUB expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'arrow_expression'0 => box
    (arrow_expression'nt, [NT logical_OR_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'arrow_expression'1 => box
    (arrow_expression'nt, [NT logical_OR_expression'nt; T RARROW't; NT arrow_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun e1 loc e0 =>
    ( [LustreAst.ARROW e0 e1 loc] )
)
  | Prod'bool_constant'0 => box
    (bool_constant'nt, [T TRUE't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.CONST_BOOL true, loc) )
)
  | Prod'bool_constant'1 => box
    (bool_constant'nt, [T FALSE't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.CONST_BOOL false, loc) )
)
  | Prod'cast_expression'0 => box
    (cast_expression'nt, [NT unary_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'cast_expression'1 => box
    (cast_expression'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT type_name'nt; T COLON't; NT cast_expression'nt; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun _5 typ loc expr _1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.CAST (fst typ) expr loc] )
)
  | Prod'clock'0 => box
    (clock'nt, [T DOT't]%list)
    (fun _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.BASE )
)
  | Prod'clock'1 => box
    (clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T ON't; NT clock'nt]%list)
    (fun id _2 clk =>
    ( LustreAst.ON clk (fst id) true )
)
  | Prod'clock'2 => box
    (clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T ONOT't; NT clock'nt]%list)
    (fun id _2 clk =>
    ( LustreAst.ON clk (fst id) false )
)
  | Prod'constant'0 => box
    (constant'nt, [T CONSTANT't]%list)
    (fun cst =>
    ( cst )
)
  | Prod'constant'1 => box
    (constant'nt, [NT bool_constant'nt]%list)
    (fun cst =>
    ( cst )
)
  | Prod'declaration'0 => box
    (declaration'nt, [NT optsemicolon'nt; T TEL't; NT equations'nt; T LET't; NT local_decl_list'nt; NT optsemicolon'nt; T RPAREN't; NT oparameter_list'nt; T LPAREN't; T RETURNS't; NT optsemicolon'nt; T RPAREN't; NT oparameter_list'nt; T LPAREN't; T VAR_NAME't; NT node_or_function'nt]%list)
    (fun _16 _15 eqns _13 locals _11 _10 oparams _8 _7 _6 _5 iparams _3 id is_node =>
    ( LustreAst.NODE
        (fst id) (fst is_node) iparams oparams locals eqns (snd is_node) )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'0 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, []%list)
    (
    ( LustreAst.FULLCK LustreAst.BASE )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'1 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T WHEN't]%list)
    (fun id _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) true )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'2 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T NOT't; T WHEN't]%list)
    (fun id _2 _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) false )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'3 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T WHENOT't]%list)
    (fun id _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) false )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'4 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [NT clock'nt; T COLONCOLON't]%list)
    (fun clk _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.FULLCK clk )
)
  | Prod'equality_expression'0 => box
    (equality_expression'nt, [NT relational_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'equality_expression'1 => box
    (equality_expression'nt, [NT relational_expression'nt; T EQ't; NT equality_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.EQ expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'equality_expression'2 => box
    (equality_expression'nt, [NT relational_expression'nt; T NEQ't; NT equality_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.NE expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'equation'0 => box
    (equation'nt, [T SEMICOLON't; NT expression'nt; T EQ't; NT pattern'nt]%list)
    (fun _4 exp loc pat =>
    ( (rev pat, exp, loc) )
)
  | Prod'equation'1 => box
    (equation'nt, [T SEMICOLON't; NT expression'nt; T EQ't; T RPAREN't; NT pattern'nt; T LPAREN't]%list)

    ( [] )

    ( eq::eqs )
)
  | Prod'equations'2 => box

    ( expr )

  | Prod'translation_unit_file'1 => box

    ( [] )

  | Prod'type_name'0 => box

  | Prod'type_name'5 => box

  | Prod'type_name'6 => box

  | Prod'type_name'7 => box

  | Prod'type_name'8 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T FLOAT32't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tfloat32, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'9 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T FLOAT64't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tfloat64, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'10 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T BOOL't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tbool, loc) )
)
  | Prod'unary_expression'0 => box
    (unary_expression'nt, [NT postfix_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )

  | Prod'unary_expression'1 => box
    (unary_expression'nt, [NT cast_expression'nt; NT unary_operator'nt]%list)
    (fun expr op =>
    ( [LustreAst.UNARY (fst op) expr (snd op)] )
)
  | Prod'unary_expression'2 => box
    (unary_expression'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT expression_list'nt; T LPAREN't; T HASH't]%list)
    (fun _4 args _2 loc =>
    (
      [LustreAst.BINARY
        LustreAst.LE
        [fold_right (fun es e => LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.ADD [e] [es] loc)
   (LustreAst.CONSTANT (LustreAst.CONST_INT LustreAst.string_zero) loc)
   (map (fun e=>LustreAst.CAST LustreAst.Tbool [e] loc)
    args)]
 [LustreAst.CONSTANT (LustreAst.CONST_INT LustreAst.string_one) loc]
 loc]
    )

  | Prod'unary_operator'0 => box
    (unary_operator'nt, [T MINUS't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.MINUS, loc) )

  | Prod'unary_operator'1 => box

    ( (LustreAst.NOT, loc) )

    ( (LustreAst.BNOT, loc) )

  | Prod'var_decl'0 => box
    (var_decl'nt, [NT declared_clock'nt; NT type_name'nt; T COLON't; NT identifier_list'nt]%list)

    ( map (fun id=> (id, (fst ty, clk, loc))) (rev ids) )

    ( vars )

Definition prod_lhs (p:production) :=
  fst (projT1 (prod_contents p)).
Definition prod_rhs_rev (p:production) :=
  snd (projT1 (prod_contents p)).
Definition prod_action (p:production) :=
  projT2 (prod_contents p).

Include MenhirLib.Grammar.Defs.

End Gram.

Module Aut <: MenhirLib.Automaton.T.

Local Obligation Tactic := let x := fresh in intro x; case x; reflexivity.

Module Gram := Gram.
Module GramDefs := Gram.

Definition nullable_nterm (nt:nonterminal) : bool :=
  match nt with
  | when_expression'nt => false
  | var_decl_list'nt => false
  | var_decl'nt => false
  | unary_operator'nt => false
  | unary_expression'nt => false
  | type_name'nt => false
  | translation_unit_file'nt => false
  | translation_unit'nt => false
  | shift_expression'nt => false
  | relational_expression'nt => false
  | primary_expression'nt => false
  | postfix_expression'nt => false
  | pattern'nt => false
  | parameter_list'nt => false
  | optsemicolon'nt => true
  | oparameter_list'nt => true
  | node_or_function'nt => false
  | multiplicative_expression'nt => false
  | logical_OR_expression'nt => false
  | logical_AND_expression'nt => false
  | local_var_decl'nt => false
  | local_decl_list'nt => true
  | local_decl'nt => false
  | inclusive_OR_expression'nt => false
  | identifier_list'nt => false
  | fby_expression'nt => false
  | expression_list'nt => false
  | expression'nt => false
  | exclusive_OR_expression'nt => false
  | equations'nt => true
  | equation'nt => false
  | equality_expression'nt => false
  | declared_clock'nt => true
  | declaration'nt => false
  | constant'nt => false
  | clock'nt => false
  | cast_expression'nt => false
  | bool_constant'nt => false
  | arrow_expression'nt => false
  | additive_expression'nt => false
  | AND_expression'nt => false
  end.

Definition first_nterm (nt:nonterminal) : list terminal :=
  match nt with
  | when_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | var_decl_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | var_decl'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | unary_operator'nt => [NOT't; MINUS't; LNOT't]%list
  | unary_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | type_name'nt => [UINT8't; UINT64't; UINT32't; UINT16't; INT8't; INT64't; INT32't; INT16't; FLOAT64't; FLOAT32't; BOOL't]%list
  | translation_unit_file'nt => [NODE't; FUNCTION't; EOF't]%list
  | translation_unit'nt => [NODE't; FUNCTION't]%list
  | shift_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | relational_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | primary_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; LPAREN't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | postfix_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; LPAREN't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | pattern'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | parameter_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | optsemicolon'nt => [SEMICOLON't]%list
  | oparameter_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | node_or_function'nt => [NODE't; FUNCTION't]%list
  | multiplicative_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | logical_OR_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | logical_AND_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | local_var_decl'nt => [VAR't]%list
  | local_decl_list'nt => [VAR't]%list
  | local_decl'nt => [VAR't]%list
  | inclusive_OR_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | identifier_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | fby_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | expression_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; MERGE't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; IFTE't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; MERGE't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; IFTE't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | exclusive_OR_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | equations'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LPAREN't; ASSERT't]%list
  | equation'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LPAREN't]%list
  | equality_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; TRUE't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; HASH't; FALSE't; CONSTANT't]%list

Inductive initstate' : Set :=
| Init'0.
Definition initstate := initstate'.

Program Instance initstateNum : MenhirLib.Alphabet.Numbered initstate :=
  { inj := fun x => match x return _ with
    | Init'0 => 1%positive
    end;
    surj := (fun n => match n return _ with
    | 1%positive => Init'0
    | _ => Init'0
    end)%Z;
    inj_bound := 1%positive }.
Instance InitStateAlph : MenhirLib.Alphabet.Alphabet initstate := _.

Include MenhirLib.Automaton.Types.

Definition start_nt (init:initstate) : nonterminal :=
  match init with
  | Init'0 => translation_unit_file'nt
  end.

  match noninitstate with
  | Nis'1 => []%list
  | Nis'2 => []%list

  | Nis'5 => []%list
  | Nis'6 => [NT translation_unit'nt]%list
  | Nis'7 => []%list
  | Nis'8 => [NT node_or_function'nt]%list
  | Nis'9 => [T VAR_NAME't; NT node_or_function'nt]%list

Module MenhirLibParser := MenhirLib.Main.Make Aut.
Theorem safe:
  MenhirLibParser.safe_validator tt = true.
Proof eq_refl true<:MenhirLibParser.safe_validator tt = true.

Theorem complete:
  MenhirLibParser.complete_validator tt = true.
Proof eq_refl true<:MenhirLibParser.complete_validator tt = true.

Definition translation_unit_file : nat -> MenhirLibParser.Inter.buffer -> MenhirLibParser.Inter.parse_result (list LustreAst.declaration) := MenhirLibParser.parse safe Aut.Init'0.

Theorem translation_unit_file_correct (log_fuel : nat) (buffer : MenhirLibParser.Inter.buffer):
  match translation_unit_file log_fuel buffer with
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Parsed_pr sem buffer_new =>
      exists word (tree : Gram.parse_tree (NT translation_unit_file'nt) word),
        buffer = MenhirLibParser.Inter.app_buf word buffer_new /\
        Gram.pt_sem tree = sem
  | _ => True
  end.
Proof.
apply MenhirLibParser.parse_correct with (init:=Aut.Init'0). Qed.

Theorem translation_unit_file_complete (log_fuel : nat) (word : list token) (buffer_end : MenhirLibParser.Inter.buffer) :
  forall tree : Gram.parse_tree (NT translation_unit_file'nt) word,
  match translation_unit_file log_fuel (MenhirLibParser.Inter.app_buf word buffer_end) with
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Fail_pr => False
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Parsed_pr output_res buffer_end_res =>
      output_res = Gram.pt_sem tree /\
      buffer_end_res = buffer_end /\ (Gram.pt_size tree <= PeanoNat.Nat.pow 2 log_fuel)%nat
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Timeout_pr => (PeanoNat.Nat.pow 2 log_fuel < Gram.pt_size tree)%nat
  end.
Proof.
apply MenhirLibParser.parse_complete with (init:=Aut.Init'0); exact complete. Qed.
